	<entry>
		<id>https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20161209000000/en</id>
		<title>Wikipedia picture of the day for December 9</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20161209000000/en"/>
				<updated>2016-12-09T00:00:00Z</updated>
		
		<summary type="html">&lt;table style=&quot;margin:0 3px 3px; width:100%; text-align:left; background-color:transparent; border-collapse: collapse;&quot;&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 0.9em 0 0;&quot;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper,_USN_(covered).jpg&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; title=&quot;Grace Hopper&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Grace Hopper&quot; src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg/300px-Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg&quot; width=&quot;300&quot; height=&quot;375&quot; srcset=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg/450px-Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ad/Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg/600px-Commodore_Grace_M._Hopper%2C_USN_%28covered%29.jpg 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;2400&quot; data-file-height=&quot;3000&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 6px 0 0&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Grace_Hopper&quot; title=&quot;Grace Hopper&quot;&gt;Grace Hopper&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (1906&amp;#8211;1992) was an American &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Computer_scientist&quot; title=&quot;Computer scientist&quot;&gt;computer scientist&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/United_States_Navy&quot; title=&quot;United States Navy&quot;&gt;United States Navy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Rear_admiral_(United_States)&quot; title=&quot;Rear admiral (United States)&quot;&gt;Rear Admiral&lt;/a&gt;. She was one of the first programmers of the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Harvard_Mark_I&quot; title=&quot;Harvard Mark I&quot;&gt;Harvard Mark I&lt;/a&gt; computer in 1944, invented the first &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Compiler&quot; title=&quot;Compiler&quot;&gt;compiler&lt;/a&gt; for a computer programming language, and helped popularize the idea of machine-independent programming languages. This led to the development of &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/COBOL&quot; title=&quot;COBOL&quot;&gt;COBOL&lt;/a&gt;, one of the first &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/High-level_programming_language&quot; title=&quot;High-level programming language&quot;&gt;high-level programming languages&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;In recognition of Hopper's contributions, the destroyer &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/USS_Hopper&quot; title=&quot;USS Hopper&quot;&gt;USS &lt;i&gt;Hopper&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is named for her, as is the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Cray_XE6&quot; title=&quot;Cray XE6&quot;&gt;Cray XE6&lt;/a&gt; &quot;Hopper&quot; supercomputer at &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/NERSC&quot; class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;NERSC&quot;&gt;NERSC&lt;/a&gt;.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;Photograph: James S. Davis&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;potd-recent&quot; style=&quot;text-align:right;&quot;&gt;
Recently featured: &lt;div class=&quot;hlist inline&quot;&gt;
