		<title>Wikipedia picture of the day for December 10</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20161210000000/en"/>
				<updated>2016-12-10T00:00:00Z</updated>
		
		<summary type="html">&lt;table style=&quot;margin:0 3px 3px; width:100%; text-align:left; background-color:transparent; border-collapse: collapse;&quot;&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 0.9em 0 0;&quot;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Puente_Pulteney,_Bath,_Inglaterra,_2014-08-12,_DD_51.JPG&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; title=&quot;Pulteney Bridge&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;Pulteney Bridge&quot; src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG/380px-Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG&quot; width=&quot;380&quot; height=&quot;253&quot; srcset=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG/570px-Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/88/Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG/760px-Puente_Pulteney%2C_Bath%2C_Inglaterra%2C_2014-08-12%2C_DD_51.JPG 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;5483&quot; data-file-height=&quot;3655&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 6px 0 0&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Pulteney_Bridge&quot; title=&quot;Pulteney Bridge&quot;&gt;Pulteney Bridge&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; is an &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Arch_bridge&quot; title=&quot;Arch bridge&quot;&gt;arch bridge&lt;/a&gt; that crosses the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/River_Avon_(Bristol)&quot; title=&quot;River Avon (Bristol)&quot;&gt;River Avon&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Bath,_Somerset&quot; title=&quot;Bath, Somerset&quot;&gt;Bath&lt;/a&gt;, England. Designed by &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Robert_Adam&quot; title=&quot;Robert Adam&quot;&gt;Robert Adam&lt;/a&gt; and completed by 1774, it connects Bath with the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Georgian_architecture&quot; title=&quot;Georgian architecture&quot;&gt;Georgian&lt;/a&gt; town of &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Bathwick&quot; title=&quot;Bathwick&quot;&gt;Bathwick&lt;/a&gt;. The Grade I &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Listed_building&quot; title=&quot;Listed building&quot;&gt;listed building&lt;/a&gt; has shops built across its full 45-metre (148&amp;#160;ft) span.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;Photograph: &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/User:Poco_a_poco&quot; title=&quot;User:Poco a poco&quot;&gt;Diego Delso&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
