		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Special:FeedItem/potd/20161213000000/en"/>
				<updated>2016-12-13T00:00:00Z</updated>
		
		<summary type="html">&lt;table style=&quot;margin:0 3px 3px; width:100%; text-align:left; background-color:transparent; border-collapse: collapse;&quot;&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 0.9em 0 0;&quot;&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/File:Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg&quot; class=&quot;image&quot; title=&quot;European robin&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;European robin&quot; src=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg/380px-Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg&quot; width=&quot;380&quot; height=&quot;304&quot; srcset=&quot;//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg/570px-Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg/760px-Erithacus_rubecula_with_cocked_head.jpg 2x&quot; data-file-width=&quot;2574&quot; data-file-height=&quot;2059&quot; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;padding:0 6px 0 0&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/European_robin&quot; title=&quot;European robin&quot;&gt;European robin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (&lt;i&gt;Erithacus rubecula&lt;/i&gt;) is a small &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Insectivorous&quot; class=&quot;mw-redirect&quot; title=&quot;Insectivorous&quot;&gt;insectivorous&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Passerine&quot; title=&quot;Passerine&quot;&gt;passerine&lt;/a&gt; bird in the &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/Old_World_flycatcher&quot; title=&quot;Old World flycatcher&quot;&gt;Old World flycatcher&lt;/a&gt; family. Around 12.5–14.0&amp;#160;cm (5.0–5.5&amp;#160;in) in length, the male and female are similar in colouration, with an orange breast and face lined with grey, brown upperparts and a whitish belly. It is found across Europe, east to Western Siberia and south to North Africa; it is sedentary in most of its range except the far north.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;Photograph: &lt;a href=&quot;/wiki/User:Baresi_franco&quot; title=&quot;User:Baresi franco&quot;&gt;Francis C. Franklin&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/small&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
